Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%mins}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} lengthways and discard the core and seeds.

Lay the pepper halves, cut-side down, onto another baking tray.

Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then roast on the top
shelf of your oven until soft and slightly charred, ~{18-20%mins}.

While everything roasts, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%grams} in a
#medium bowl{} with the @plain flour{1%tbsp} and half the @Cajun spice mix{1/2%sachet}.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat completely in the flour.

> See pantry for flour amount.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high
heat.

Once hot, add the chicken and fry until cooked through, ~{8-10%mins} total.
Turn every 2-3 mins.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.
> It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}.

Return the pan to low heat and add the @sweet chilli sauce{64%grams}, a splash
of @water{1%splash} and the remaining @Cajun spice mix{1/2%sachet}. Stir until
well combined, ~{1%min}.

Return the cooked chicken to the pan, turning gently to coat in the sauce.
Set aside.

In a medium bowl, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%grams}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and
@olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

> See pantry for vinegar and olive oil amounts.

Halve the @burger buns{2}. Pop onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm
through, ~{2-3%mins}.

Just before you're ready to serve, add the @wild rocket{20%grams} to the bowl
and toss to coat in the dressing.

When everything's ready, pop the buns onto your plates and spread the
@mayonnaise{3%tbsp} over both cut sides.

Stack each bun base with a roasted pepper half and the glazed chicken. Spoon
over any remaining sweet chilli glaze from the pan and sandwich shut with the
bun lid.

Serve with the chips and rocket salad alongside. Enjoy!